<html xmlns:tal="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/tal"
      xmlns:metal="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/metal"
      i18n:domain="plone">
<body>
<metal:portlet define-macro="portlet">

<tal:comment tal:replace="nothing">
Catherine Williams created this file to:
- make a portlet containing links that should appear on all Huck Institutes grad program pages below the education section
- if it can't find an faq or how-to-apply page/folder at the current level, it'll keep going up until it finds one
- This portlet should be used within each graduate program, in left_slots, under the navigation portlet
- This use assumes that there is a single application form for all graduate programs
- And a single FAQ folder (which might contain subfolders...)
- This will render an error if there is no "apply", "faq" or "education" folder in the path from context to portal root
</tal:comment>

<div tal:define="wherearewe context/absolute_url;
				inFaq python:'faq' in wherearewe;
				inApply python:'apply' in wherearewe">	
				
	<dl  id="customNavTree" class="portlet">
		<dd class="portletItem portletLastItem" >
	
			<ul class="portletNavigationTree navTreeLevel0">
				<li tal:condition="not:inApply" class="navTreeItem visualNoMarker apply">
					<a href="" tal:attributes="href context/apply/absolute_url; title context/apply/Description" class="visualIconPadding">How to apply</a>
				</li>
				<li tal:condition="not:inFaq" class="navTreeItem visualNoMarker">
					<a href="" tal:attributes="href context/faq/absolute_url; title context/faq/Description" class="visualIconPadding">Frequently-asked questions</a>
				</li>
				<li  class="navTreeItem visualNoMarker">
					<a tal:attributes="href context/education/absolute_url; title context/education/Description" class="visualIconPadding">List all Huck Institutes graduate degree programs</a>
				</li>
			</ul>
		</dd>


	</dl>
</div>
</metal:portlet>
</body>
</html>
